name: Spring Thaw
description:
I like to walk and observe surroundings. Some day I stopped listening to loud music in noise-cancelling DJ headphones, stopped listening to podcasts but paid more attention to the world I am walking in.

Since I made a shift I see more around me. In the same routes, places, same 'boring' walks. There is much to see if you get out of your head.

This photo has a lot to see. It was made in spring 2017 and edited a little bit (crop and colors, contrast).

I can explain how I see this image and _what_ I see in it but I will leave it behind. I let every observer find something for themselves in this photo. (If you wish to hear about my perception you can ask me)

I only say that it was the very beginning of spring in Estonia.

Twitter: @feelosopher777
